Shaken 'n' Stirred is an album by former Led Zeppelin vocalist Robert Plant
released in 1985 on the Es Paranza label. It featured his second Mainstream
Rock Tracks top hit, "Little by Little", which was #1 on the chart for two
weeks.

Rhino Entertainment released a remastered edition of the album, with one
bonus track, on 20 March 2007.
